President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has delegated authority to the Secretary of State to direct the drawdown of up to $1 billion in defense articles and services, as well as military education and training, to provide assistance to Ukraine. This delegation of authority is made under section 506(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. The Secretary of State is also authorized to make the necessary determinations required under this section to direct the drawdown. The memorandum also instructs the Secretary of State to publish this information in the Federal Register.